video source: Annenberg Public Policy Center at the University of Pennsylvania in collab w VMP, review by kobayashi & haraguchi in communicative & integrative biology. optimism despite recent cuts of billions of dollars from NIH funding by restricting indirect costs (equipment, operations, maintenance, hazardous waste management, support staff) to 15%, although the average indirect cost rate for organizations receiving grants from the NIH was ~28% "How a living cell responds to exogenous materials is one of the fundamental questions in the life sciences. In particular, understanding the mechanisms by which a cell recognizes exogenous double-stranded DNA (dsDNA) is important for immunology research because it will facilitate the control of pathogen infections that entail the presence of exogenous dsDNA in the cytoplasm of host cells. Several cytosolic dsDNA sensor proteins that trigger innate immune responses have been identified and the downstream signaling pathways have been investigated. However, the events that occur at the site of exogenous dsDNA when it is exposed to the cytosol of the host cell remain unknown. Using dsDNA-coated polystyrene beads incorporated into living cells, we recently found that barrier-to-autointegration factor (BAF) binds to the exogenous dsDNA immediately after its appearance in the cytosol and plays a role in DNA avoidance of autophagy. Our findings reveal a novel pathway in which BAF plays a key role in the detection of and response to exogenous dsDNA." #cellbiology #genetics #biology #dna

Spicy Honey Garlic Chicken Thighs Ingredients: â€¢ 4 chicken thighs (bone-in, skin-on) â€¢ 1/4 cup honey â€¢ 3 cloves garlic, minced â€¢ 2 tbsp soy sauce â€¢ 1 tbsp olive oil â€¢ 1 tsp chili flakes (adjust to taste) â€¢ Salt and pepper to taste â€¢ Fresh parsley, chopped (for garnish) Instructions: 1. Preheat your oven to 400Â°F (200Â°C). 2. Season the chicken thighs with salt and pepper on both sides. 3. Heat the olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat. Place the chicken thighs skin-side down and cook for 5-7 minutes until the skin is crispy and golden. Flip the thighs and cook for an additional 5 minutes. 4. Getting big in the gym involves a combination of consistent strength training, proper nutrition, and adequate recovery. Hereâ€™s a concise guide to achieving muscle growth: 1. Strength Training: Focus on compound movements like squats, deadlifts, bench presses, and pull-ups, which engage multiple muscle groups and stimulate muscle growth. Aim to lift heavy weights with low to moderate repetitions (6-12 reps) and progressively increase the weight over time. Include isolation exercises to target specific muscles. 2. Training Frequency: Train each muscle group 2-3 times a week. This can be achieved through split routines (e.g., upper/lower body splits) or full-body workouts, ensuring balanced development and sufficient stimulus for muscle growth. 3. Nutrition: Consume a calorie surplus, meaning you eat more calories than you burn. Focus on protein-rich foods (1.6-2.2 grams of protein per kilogram of body weight) to support muscle repair and growth. Incorporate complex carbohydrates and healthy fats to fuel workouts and recovery. Stay hydrated and consider supplements like whey protein, creatine, and branched-chain amino acids (BCAAs) if needed. 4. Recovery: Prioritize sleep (7-9 hours per night) and rest days to allow muscles to repair and grow. Avoid overtraining, which can lead to injuries and hinder progress. 5. Consistency and Patience: Building muscle takes time. Stay consistent with your workouts and nutrition plan, track your progress, and make adjustments as needed. 6. Proper Form and Technique: Ensure proper form to maximize effectiveness and minimize injury risk. Consider working with a trainer to perfect your technique. By following these principles, you can achieve significant muscle growth and build a strong, muscular physique over time.

Certainly, here is the information on the Volkswagen Beetle: The Volkswagen Beetle, also known as the Volkswagen Type 1, is an iconic car produced by the German automaker Volkswagen (VW) from 1938 until 2003. Renowned for its distinctive shape and enduring popularity, the Beetle is one of the most recognizable cars in automotive history. It was initially available as a two-door sedan, with later variations including convertibles. The Beetle featured an air-cooled, rear-mounted, flat-four engine, with displacements ranging from 1.1 liters in early models to 1.6 liters in later versions. It typically had a 4-speed manual transmission, although semi-automatic and fully automatic options were introduced in later models. The Beetle's design focused on simplicity and reliability, making it a favorite among a wide range of drivers. Its legacy continues to influence car design and popular culture to this day.

The 2024 Aston Martin DB12 represents a significant advancement in the brand's grand touring lineup, earning the title of "Super Tourer." Here are the key details: 1. **Performance**: It is powered by a twin-turbocharged 4.0-liter V8 engine, generating 671 horsepower and 590 lb-ft of torque. This enables a 0 to 60 mph time of 3.5 seconds and a top speed of 202 mph. 2. **Chassis and Handling**: The DB12 features a stiffer body and chassis compared to its predecessor, the DB11. It includes wider front and rear tracks, Bilstein DTX adaptive shocks, and a reprogrammed eight-speed automatic transmission. It rides on Michelin Pilot Sport S 5 tires, which are designed for enhanced grip and stability. 3. **Braking**: The car comes standard with cast-iron discs but offers an optional Carbon Ceramic Brake (CCB) package, which reduces unsprung mass by 27 kg and provides superior performance at high temperatures. 4. **Technology and Interior**: The interior is equipped with dual 10.3-inch displays, over-the-air software updates, and compatibility with the Aston Martin app. The infotainment system has been modernized, though some reviews suggest it is still catching up to rivals. 5. **Design**: The exterior features a bold and assertive design, with options for 21-inch forged alloy wheels in various styles and finishes. These design choices also focus on reducing weight and improving performance. 6. **Driver Assistance and Modes**: The DB12 includes an advanced Electronic Stability Programme (ESP) with modes for various conditions (Wet, On, Track, Off) and five drive modes (GT, Sport, Sport+, Wet, Individual), allowing for tailored driving dynamics. Overall, the Aston Martin DB12 merges luxury with high performance and modern technology, making it a standout in the high-performance grand touring segment.

### What is Fire? Fire is a chemical reaction called combustion, involving the rapid oxidation of fuel in the presence of oxygen, releasing heat and light. #### The Fire Triangle Fire requires three elements: 1. **Fuel**: Combustible material like wood or gasoline. 2. **Oxygen**: From the air. 3. **Heat**: To start and sustain the reaction. #### Types of Fire - **Wood Fires**: Burn organic material. - **Gasoline Fires**: Highly flammable. - **Electrical Fires**: From electrical malfunctions. #### How Fire Works Heat causes fuel molecules to break apart, forming free radicals that react with oxygen, creating a self-sustaining chain reaction. The flames are hot gases emitting light. #### Colors of Fire - **Yellow/Orange Flames**: Common in wood fires. - **Blue Flames**: Indicate higher temperatures, often in gas stoves. - **Red Flames**: Cooler parts of the fire. #### Fire Safety Understanding fire helps in using tools like fire extinguishers and water to control or extinguish it by removing one of the fire triangleâ€™s elements. ### Conclusion Fire is a vital chemical reaction, essential for warmth, cooking, and technology, but requires careful management for safety.

The Porsche engineers knew exactly what their objective was: to make the new 911 GT2 RS the most powerful Porsche for the road. Objective achieved. The water-cooled six-cylinder bi-turbo Boxer engine with four-valve technology, variable turbine geometry (VTG) and VarioCam Plus delivers its power through the rear axle. From a displacement of 3,600 cm3, it generates an enormous 456 kW (620 hp) at an engine speed of 6,500 rpm. The maximum torque of 700 Nm is available from 2,250 rpm. From 0 to 100 km/h (62 mph) takes just 3.5 seconds. To 200 km/h (124 mph) only 9.8 seconds, and to 300 km/h (186 mph) just 28.9 seconds. Maximum boost pressure is not reached until a speed of 330 km/h (205 mph). The weight-to-power ratio that is essential for this kind of performance is just 2.21 kg/hp. A consistent supply of oil to the engine - even at high cornering speeds - is achieved using a dry sump lubrication system with a separate engine oil reservoir. The oil is cooled by an oil-water heat exchanger.

Mythical reel pull? To cook a tender steak, itâ€™s crucial to start with a good quality piece of meat. Look for cuts that are well-marbled with fat, such as ribeye or New York strip. Before cooking, allow the steak to come to room temperature, as this ensures even cooking. Season the steak generously with salt and pepper, or your preferred steak seasoning, and let it sit for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to penetrate the meat. For the cooking process, preheat a heavy skillet or grill pan over high heat. The pan should be hot enough that it sizzles when you place the steak on it. Sear the steak for a few minutes on each side to create a caramelized crust. Then, reduce the heat to medium and continue cooking to your desired level of doneness. Use a meat thermometer to achieve the perfect temperature: 120Â°F for rare, 130Â°F for medium-rare, 140Â°F for medium, and so on. Remember to let the steak rest for a few minutes before slicing it, as this allows the juices to redistribute and results in a more tender and flavorful steak. Another method to ensure a tender steak is to marinate it before cooking. Create a marinade using ingredients like olive oil, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, and herbs. Place the steak in a resealable bag and pour the marinade over it, making sure it is evenly coated. Let it marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, or overnight for maximum flavor. When itâ€™s time to cook, remove the steak from the marinade and pat it dry with paper towels. Discard the marinade as it may contain harmful bacteria. Preheat your grill or skillet over medium-high heat and cook the steak following the same searing and cooking instructions as mentioned before. The marinade not only adds flavor but also helps to tenderize the meat by breaking down the muscle fibers. By following these techniques, you can cook a steak that is not only delicious but also incredibly tender. Whether you choose to sear it or marinate it, remember that the key lies in using high-quality meat and giving it the proper time and attention it deserves. #reels #brainrot #dankmemes

Hereâ€™s a classic brownie recipe that yields rich and fudgy brownies: ### Ingredients: - 1 cup (225g) unsalted butter - 1 cup (200g) granulated sugar - 1 cup (200g) brown sugar, packed - 4 large eggs - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 1 cup (125g) all-purpose flour - 1 cup (85g) unsweetened cocoa powder - 1/2 teaspoon salt - 1 cup (175g) chocolate chips or chunks (optional) ### Instructions: 1. **Preheat Oven**: Preheat your oven to 350Â°F (175Â°C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking pan or line it with parchment paper. 2. **Melt Butter**: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. Once melted, remove from heat and let it cool slightly. 3. **Mix Sugars and Eggs**: In a large mixing bowl, combine the granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add the melted butter to the sugars and mix well. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla extract. 4. **Combine Dry Ingredients**: In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. 5. **Add Chocolate Chips**: Fold in the chocolate chips or chunks if using. 6. **Bake**: Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly. Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter). 7. **Cool and Serve**: Allow the brownies to cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving. Enjoy your homemade brownies!

Here's a classic brownie recipe that yields rich and fudgy brownies: ### Ingredients: - 1 cup (225g) unsalted butter - 1 cup (200g) granulated sugar - 1 cup (200g) brown sugar, packed 4 large eggs 1 teaspoon vanilla extract 1 cup (125g) all-purpose flour - 1 cup (85g) unsweetened cocoa powder 1/2 teaspoon salt -1 cup (175g) chocolate chips or chunks Instructions: 1. **Preheat Oven**: Preheat your oven to 350Â°F (175Â°C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking pan or line it with parchment paper. 2. **Melt Butter**: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. Once melted, remove from heat and let it cool slightly. 3. **Mix Sugars and Eggs**: In a large mixing bowl, combine the granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add the melted butter to the sugars and mix well. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla extract. 4. **Combine Dry Ingredients**: In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. 5. **Add Chocolate Chips**: Fold in the chocolate chips or chunks if using. 6. **Bake**: Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly. Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not wet batter). 7. **Cool and Serve**: Allow the brownies to cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving.

real String theory is a theoretical framework in physics that aims to reconcile general relativity and quantum mechanics, the two pillars of modern physics. At its core, string theory proposes that the fundamental building blocks of the universe are not point-like particles, but rather one-dimensional â€œstringsâ€ that vibrate at specific frequencies. These vibrations determine the properties of particles, such as mass and charge, much like the different notes produced by a vibrating guitar string ğŸ¸. One of the most intriguing aspects of string theory is its requirement for additional dimensions beyond the familiar three dimensions of space and one dimension of time. In fact, string theory suggests the existence of up to 11 dimensions! These extra dimensions are thought to be compactified or curled up so small that they are not easily observable in our everyday experience ğŸŒ€. String theory has also given rise to the concept of â€œbranes,â€ multi-dimensional objects on which strings can attach. Our entire universe could be a 3-dimensional brane floating in a higher-dimensional space, with other branes potentially hosting parallel universes ğŸª. Despite its elegance and potential, string theory remains highly speculative. It has yet to produce testable predictions that can be experimentally verified. Nonetheless, it offers a tantalizing glimpse into the deeper structure of reality and continues to inspire physicists in their quest for a unified theory of everything. Whether or not string theory ultimately proves correct, its influence on theoretical physics and the way we think about the universe is undeniable. ğŸŒŒâœ¨

That one mf credit: unknown (dm) Here's a classic brownie recipe along with instructions: **Ingredients:** - 1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter - 2 1/4 cups granulated sugar - 4 large eggs - 1 1/4 cups unsweetened cocoa powder - 1 teaspoon salt - 1 teaspoon baking powder - 1 teaspoon vanilla extract - 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour - 1 cup chocolate chips (optional) **Instructions:** 1. Preheat your oven to 350Â°F (175Â°C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking pan or line it with parchment paper. 2. In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over low heat. 3. Stir in the sugar until combined. Remove from heat and let it cool slightly. 4. In a large bowl, beat the eggs together. 5. Gradually add the melted butter and sugar mixture to the eggs, stirring continuously. 6. Sift together the cocoa powder, salt, baking powder, and flour in a separate bowl. 7. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined. Be careful not to overmix. 8. Stir in the vanilla extract and chocolate chips if using. 9. Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly. 10. Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs. 11. Remove the brownies from the oven and let them cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares. 12. Serve and enjoy your homemade brownies! Feel free to adjust the recipe to your taste by adding nuts, extra chocolate chips, or a sprinkle of sea salt on top before baking.
